b'' b'what a great day! got back home last night from some fantastic skiing' b'in colorado, and put the battery back in the fxstc. cleaned the plugs,' b'opened up the petcock, waited a minute, hit the starter, and bingo it' b'started up like a charm! spent a restless night anticipating the first' b'ride du saison, and off i went this morning to get my state inspection' b'done. now my bike is stock (so far) except for hd slash-cut pipes, and' b'all went well with my new hampshire state inspection (meaning all my' b'lights worked ok) until the dude produces a decibel meter and tells me' b'about the new nh law about mc noise.....huh? sez i....and he has me' b'start her up and rev to about rpm....i fail cuz i register db,' b'and the max allowed is if i fail with these pipes, there are gonna' b'be a whole lotta seriously pissed off bikers round here when they go' b'for inspection.' b'' b'*&%^*$%*^*%*&' b'' b'but hey, its a new experience! i have never really felt like a menace' b'to society before! i parked, dismounted and walked in to my building' b'with a slight swagger to my step, and a narrow lidded look... i sensed' b'my faculty colleagues unease with my new intimidating status...and' b"women's glances seemed to linger just a little longer....or perhaps" b'that was my imagination.......*sigh*' b'' b'now i need to install my new bub pipes and single fire ignition....i' b'wonder how i will do after that!?' b'' b"russ hughes fxstc dod# 6022(10e20)" b'"love ...yeah, that\'s the feeling you get when you like something' b'as much as your motorcycle."' b'--sonny barger (as told to me by ed campbell,' b'who has an old friend who was there at the time)' 